[Name] libao
[Summary] A cross-platform audio library.
[License] GNU General Public License (GPL)
[Description] Libao is a cross-platform audio library that
allows programs to  output audio using a simple
API on a wide variety of platforms. It currently
supports null output, WAV files, AU files, OSS
(Open Sound System, used on Linux and FreeBSD),
esd, ALSA, AIX, Sun/NetBSD/OpenBSD, IRIX, and NAS
(Network Audio Server).
[Homepage] http://www.xiph.org/ao/
